The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 October is 81,444 (9,386.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 2,544 new confirmed cases (293.2 new cases per 100,000). There is no change in cases compared to those confirmed in the previous week (seven days to 01 October).
